      <part part_index="1" name="Top film festivals in Europe" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="124">
            	<![CDATA[
Europe has many influential and well-known film festivals. Let's take a quick look.
Venice International Film Festival
The Venice International Film Festival (威尼斯国际电影节) is the oldest film festival in the world.
The festival takes place every year in late August or early September on the island of Lido, Venice, Italy.
The principal award of the festival is the Golden Lion (金狮奖). It is awarded to the best film, and the Silver Lion is for the best director.
Cannes Film Festival
The Cannes Film Festival (戛纳电影节) is one of the most popular film festivals across the world.
The festival takes place every year in May in Cannes, France. It represents one of the most respected film awards in the whole film industry, especially in the European film industry.
           	]]>
            </article>
